description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity for Registered Nurses has become available to join our friendly team on Wintle ward at the Warneford Hospital. We are a 16 bed Female Adult Acute admission ward.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are interested in hearing from dual or mental health registered staff. If you are a preceptee the trust now has a specific 2 year course for newly qualified Nurses and Allied Health Professionals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are working towards the recovery model, have achieved our AIMS accreditation and received a good rating from CQC.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is scope for learning with our further education partners and the opportunity to take part in research with our Research partners and with our ward Psychologist including enhancing physical health care, psychosocial interventions, working with carers and managing Violence and aggression.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for energetic and enthusiastic staff with a can do attitude and a passion for working with female patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Trust offers short term accommodation solutions for those looking to relocate to the area, and we are able to offer full time, part time and flexible working arrangements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Harkirtan Tanday Ward Manager or Tony Walmsley Matron on 01865 902481.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
